What you suggest ?

@arunmahadevan Yeah, the second sentence was unclear, but my first sentence:

> It doesn't seem safe to add the --old-consumer option and change the default in one release.

Was what I meant. Normally the way stuff like this is handled is to ensure the new option is made available in one release without changing defaults so that scripts don't break but you can warn users that there will be a change, then change the default in a subsequent release. You can try to make both work based on required arguments, though that makes things a bit messier (and in which case the `--new-consumer` and `--old-consumer` arguments are actually superfluous and only serve to make the decision explicit since they have other mutually exclusive required arguments).
